## Global Coding Conventions — LLM-IFC Project

### Environment
- Two Python envs: system venv (MCP server) vs Blender embedded Python. NEVER cross-install.
- Use `uv` for dependency management, not pip.
- Python 3.10+ with type hints on ALL function signatures.

### Code Style
- Module docstrings on every .py file.
- Use `logging` module, NEVER `print()` (breaks MCP stdio transport).
- All IFC operations via `ifcopenshell.api.run()`.
- JSON-serializable inputs/outputs for any MCP-facing code.

### IFC Conventions
- IFC4 schema only. Coordinates in meters. Z-axis up.
- Call `save_and_load_ifc()` after any mutation to the Blender scene.
- Never use `execute_blender_code` in automated agent flows.

### Testing & Reporting
- All new functionality needs a test in `tests/`.
- Golden tests must pass before merging to main.
- Validation reports go to `reports/` directory.
- Commit messages follow Conventional Commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, `test:`.
